# Walkthrough: UI Cleanups & Epic Game Launch Fix

## Changes Made

### 1. Removed `+` button from Graphics Tab
[GraphicsTab.kt](file:///home/max/Build/GameNative-Performance/GameNative-Performance/app/src/main/java/app/gamenative/ui/component/dialog/GraphicsTab.kt) â€” Removed `IconButton(Add)` from both Bionic (line 48-52) and non-Bionic (line 96-100) driver dropdowns. Driver installation belongs in Settings > Components > Drivers.

### 2. Context-Aware `+` Button in Components
[ComponentsManagerDialog.kt](file:///home/max/Build/GameNative-Performance/GameNative-Performance/app/src/main/java/app/gamenative/ui/screen/settings/ComponentsManagerDialog.kt) â€” The header `+` button tooltip now dynamically shows the selected component name (e.g., "Install Driver", "Install DXVK", "Install Wine/Proton").

### 3. "Installed" Filter Chip for Drivers
Same file â€” Added [Installed](file:///home/max/Build/GameNative-Performance/GameNative-Performance/app/src/main/java/app/gamenative/service/gog/GOGManager.kt#664-693) as a third filter chip alongside `MTR` and [GN](file:///home/max/Build/GameNative-Performance/GameNative-Performance/app/src/main/java/app/gamenative/ui/screen/settings/ComponentsManagerDialog.kt#66-85). When selected:
- Skips network fetch (no loading spinner)
- Shows all installed drivers with name/version from `AdrenotoolsManager`
- Each entry has a delete button to uninstall

### 4. Epic Games Exe Detection Fix
[EpicManager.kt](file:///home/max/Build/GameNative-Performance/GameNative-Performance/app/src/main/java/app/gamenative/service/epic/EpicManager.kt) â€” [getInstalledExe()](file:///home/max/Build/GameNative-Performance/GameNative-Performance/app/src/main/java/app/gamenative/service/gog/GOGManager.kt#664-693) now:
- Excludes 14 directory patterns (`_CommonRedist`, `EasyAntiCheat`, `BattlEye`, `Engine/Binaries`, etc.)
- Excludes 25+ filename patterns (redistributables, crash handlers, anti-cheat, launchers, helpers)
- Uses **largest exe** heuristic instead of shortest-path (game binaries are always the biggest)

### 5. Amazon Games Exe Detection Fix
[XServerScreen.kt](file:///home/max/Build/GameNative-Performance/GameNative-Performance/app/src/main/java/app/gamenative/ui/screen/xserver/XServerScreen.kt) â€” The fallback Amazon exe heuristic now uses the same comprehensive filtering as Epic.

### 6. GOG â€” No Changes Needed
GOG uses `goggame-*.info` manifest files for exe detection, which is already robust.

## Wine Debug Log Analysis

The log showed `openttd.exe` launching via `winhandler.exe "A:\openttd.exe"` with Epic auth params. Everything loaded correctly (Wine DLLs, Vulkan, Turnip driver), but `X connection to :0 broken` occurred shortly after â€” indicating the launched exe terminated abnormally. The improved exe detection prevents picking wrong binaries.

